	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />From all my experience, clones just darken a bit too much with the emphasis bits compared to the real NES.  For example, with all bits on, the NES would be at 80% brightness or so, and clones at 65% or 70%.
<br />
<br />That's all, just a stronger effect.  Not a game-ruiner like the RGB PPU.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


