	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Considering how limited as the NES palette is in hues/luminances, I very see valid reasons for using the emphasis bits to adjust it slightly for your game's color design, if you really want to make your game look as good as possible.
<br />
<br />Than again, for the sorry people who only have clones, it could be good to include a clone detection routine (trying out lots of the weird side-effects of the NES hardware that very few clones should support) and disabling their use in this case. And/or provide a menu to toggle their use on/off.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


